Stay Home & Treat Your Hair💕
We have been using curd as a hair growth remedy since FOREVER. It helps us keep our scalp hydrated, fight hair loss and dandruff. We prefer to add egg and honey if we do not have enough time to keep it overnight. 
But nothing beats sleeping with it for us! 

Here's a Step by Step:

Apply Hung Curd (Dahi) on your scalp and length.
Leave it for an hour.
Rinse just with water. (Only water can't stress this enough)
Let it stay overnight.
Shampoo and Condition the next day.
Followed by Hair serum

Feel free to share your experience in the comment section below. Tage me in your post if you try this!

Treating your hair right is exactly what the doctor ordered. 

Since the past four days, I’ve done nothing other than being cooped up in bed and allowing anxiety to take the best of me. 
Ultimately, I got out and chose to do something that gives me immense happiness.

I try to do it once in two weeks and have been doing it for the past 2-3 years. And through my experience, it's not only accelerated my hair growth but has also enhanced my natural texture. 

Give this vitamins, minerals rich recipe a try and, feel free to share your experience in the comment section below. Simply soak your hair in rice water, and voila!

✨Pre-Hair Wash | Nighttime Routine✨

Few important things I did not mention in the reel:

Never apply oil to unclean hair + wet hair 
I always apply warm oil
Too much oil will weigh your tresses down, so remember less is more
I tie my hair in a bun but not too tight as it leads to hair fall

Haircare is rarely a one-size-fits-all situation. So if there is anything you would do differently, feel free to let me know in the comment section below. 

All questions and personal experiences are welcomed in the comment section. Lets make this a page where we can learn from each other and grow💕
